author: Mike DuPont
title: WATCH: Tech's 308-pound OL Le'Raven Clark barrels across end zone on two-point attempt
text:
Although the status of senior left tackle Le'Raven Clark is unknown at this point, it's certain the 6-foot-6, 309-pound four-year starter will depart Texas Tech with a plethora of memories.
Among the memories for Clark is a two-point conversion attempt in which the offensive line took to their stances near the hash marks while the ball was placed in the middle of the field.
What happens next is every portly football player's dream: Clark lines up offset behind the linemen and catches a lateral before barreling three yards for a successful two-point conversion that put Texas Tech ahead 11-0 in the second quarter.
Watch as Le'Raven Clark houses the 2-point conversion, to put Tech up by 11! #LetTheBigDogEat #WreckEm http://t.co/LvifmydUXm
â” TechGameday (@TechGameday) October 17, 2015 The Red Raiders felt the impact of Clark's absence. Sophomore quarterback Patrick Mahomes II was sacked five times after being sacked only twice through the first six contests.
